display: Specifies the container as a flex container.


flex-direction: Defines the main axis of the flex container.


flex-wrap: Controls wrapping of flex items when they exceed the container's width or height.


justify-content: Aligns flex items along the main axis of the container.


align-items: Aligns flex items along the cross axis of the container.


align-content: Aligns wrapped lines of flex items when there is extra space in the cross axis.



order: Specifies the order of flex items.


flex-grow: Specifies how much a flex item should grow relative to the rest of the flex items.


flex-shrink: Specifies how much a flex item should shrink relative to the rest of the flex items.


flex-basis: Specifies the initial size of a flex item before remaining space is distributed.


flex: Shorthand for flex-grow, flex-shrink, and flex-basis.


align-self: Overrides align-items for specific flex items.